# Autotask API Entity Overview

## Introduction
Autotask's REST API provides access to various business entities through standardised endpoints. Each entity represents a specific business object with its own properties, relationships, and operations.

## Entity Types

### Core Business Entities
- Accounts
- Contacts
- Opportunities
- Projects
- Tickets
- Tasks
- Time Entries
- Contracts

### Supporting Entities
- Products
- Services
- Resources
- Configurations
- Documents
- Notes

## Entity Properties

### Common Fields
All entities include these standard fields:
- `id`: Unique identifier
- `createDate`: UTC timestamp of creation
- `lastModifiedDate`: UTC timestamp of last update
- `userDefinedFields`: Custom field collection

### Field Types
- Text (string)
- Numbers (integer/decimal)
- Dates (UTC format)
- Boolean
- Picklist (enumerated values)
- References (foreign keys)

## Entity Relationships

### Parent-Child Relationships
- Accounts → Contacts
- Projects → Tasks
- Tickets → Time Entries

### Many-to-Many Relationships
- Contracts ↔ Services
- Resources ↔ Projects
- Products ↔ Configurations

## Entity Operations

### Standard Operations
- GET: Retrieve entity details
- POST: Create new entities
- PUT: Update entire entity
- PATCH: Partial entity updates
- DELETE: Remove entities

### Collection Operations
- Query multiple entities
- Filter results
- Sort and page data
- Include related entities

## Best Practices

### Performance Optimisation
- Request only needed fields
- Use appropriate page sizes
- Implement caching where suitable
- Follow rate limiting guidelines

### Data Integrity
- Validate required fields
- Check field constraints
- Handle dependencies correctly
- Maintain referential integrity

